commentary: Miller to Taylor, no run a huge appeal for a caught behind but the umpire says not out. I think he nicked that. Will West Indies review? They will. Ramdin has asked for it. Taylor stayed back and tries dab the ball late, there's a certain noise as the ball passes the bat. But there's nothing on hotspot. A tricky one for the umpire. It's over to realtime snicko now ... there's a smudge of a noise on real time snicko. What will the third umpire do? Will he overturn the on-field umpire's decision based on the noise and the small spike on real time snicko? He does not. Taylor bats on. Not enough evidence to overturn the decision.
